{"key":"processedPost-10184313","value":{"id":10184313,"first":10152735,"last":10184995,"when":1239992318,"utime":"04/17/09 09:18 PM","content":"If it can be calibrated, it's fine.&nbsp; Re-calibrate weekly until it settles down.&nbsp; <br /><br />I still don't know what that silly thing you bought first is.&nbsp; It's labeled a 'hydrometer', but hydrometers don't measure humidity.&nbsp; A hydrometer measures specific gravity and is what is used to test the antifreeze solution in cars.&nbsp; The package says it's used to measure 'humility', but unless you're confessing your sins to a priest in your car, I see no need for a humility meter. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif\" alt=\":shrug:\" title=\":shrug:\"/><br />RR","title":"Re: Cheap Hydrometer? What Do U Think about This??","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}